==English==

===Noun phrase===
'''postage stamp'''

# A small piece of printed paper stuck on an item to be mailed, indicating that [[postage]] has been paid.
#: ''The stamps on the letters from overseas were almost as interesting as the letters themselves.''
# (''colloquial'') A very small area.
#: ''We have just a postage stamp of a back garden.''

